What Is Buyer Intent Data and Why It Matters in 2026
Buyer intent data refers to digital signals and behavioral indicators that reveal when a prospect is actively researching solutions in your industry. These signals might include website visits to your competitor's pages, downloads of relevant whitepapers, engagement with industry content, search queries, or participation in industry webinars.

The fundamental reason this matters is straightforward: timing is everything in B2B sales. A prospect who is actively researching solutions is exponentially more likely to engage meaningfully with your sales team than one who isn't thinking about a purchase yet. Traditional outreach methods cast a wide net reaching thousands of prospects in the hopes that some percentage might eventually need what you're selling. Intent-driven strategies are surgical by comparison, focusing resources on prospects who have already demonstrated active buying behavior.

